00:39.873 --> 00:42.205
<i>This is our land.</i>

00:43.043 --> 00:45.238
<i>A land of peace and of plenty.</i>

00:46.613 --> 00:48.410
<i>A land of harmony and hope.</i>

00:50.217 --> 00:52.549
<i>This is our land.</i>

00:53.520 --> 00:55.420
<i>Oceania.</i>

00:57.591 --> 00:59.718
<i>These are our people.</i>

01:00.961 --> 01:05.193
<i>The workers, the strivers, the builders.</i>

01:09.603 --> 01:12.003
<i>These are our people.</i>

01:12.839 --> 01:16.673
<i>The builders of our world, struggling...</i>

01:17.210 --> 01:19.906
<i>fighting, bleeding...</i>

01:21.148 --> 01:22.581
<i>dying.</i>

01:22.983 --> 01:27.283
<i>On the streets of our cities
and on the far-flung battlefields.</i>

01:28.088 --> 01:31.353
<i>Fighting against the mutilation
of our hopes and dreams.</i>

01:37.197 --> 01:38.630
<i>Who are they?</i>

01:39.432 --> 01:42.333
<i>Eurasia! Eurasia!</i>

01:44.104 --> 01:46.368
<i>They are the dark armies.</i>

01:48.041 --> 01:51.238
<i>The dark, murdering armies of Eurasia.</i>

01:53.713 --> 01:56.614
<i>In the barren deserts of Africa and India...</i>

01:57.017 --> 01:58.985
<i>on the oceans of Australasia...</i>

01:59.085 --> 02:02.543
<i>courage, strength, and youth are sacrificed.</i>

02:03.323 --> 02:08.192
<i>Sacrificed to barbarians,
whose only honor is atrocity.</i>

02:13.733 --> 02:16.133
<i>But even as we grasp at victory...</i>

02:16.469 --> 02:19.302
<i>there is a cancer, an evil tumor...</i>

02:19.873 --> 02:23.274
<i>growing, spreading in our midst.</i>

02:24.110 --> 02:26.772
<i>Shout, shout...</i>

02:26.947 --> 02:28.812
<i>shout out his name!</i>

02:29.182 --> 02:31.207
Goldstein!

02:34.721 --> 02:37.451
<i>Nothing the Party says is true.</i>

02:37.891 --> 02:40.359
<i>Nothing the Party does is good.</i>

02:41.328 --> 02:43.922
<i>Even the war itself isn't real.</i>

02:45.265 --> 02:47.927
<i>The Party wants you to believe
we are at war...</i>

02:48.034 --> 02:52.095
<i>so as to channel your aggressions
away from their rightful target...</i>

02:52.205 --> 02:53.536
<i>the Party.</i>

02:55.008 --> 02:56.771
<i>Big Brother is not real.</i>

02:58.144 --> 03:00.942
<i>He is pure fiction, created by the Party.</i>

03:01.648 --> 03:03.809
<i>The real rulers of the State...</i>

03:03.917 --> 03:06.977
<i>are unknown, faceless manipulators...</i>

03:07.087 --> 03:09.214
<i>who, because they are not known...</i>

03:09.322 --> 03:12.814
<i>are able to wield power
without let or hindrance.</i>

03:14.361 --> 03:18.229
<i>People of Oceania, you are being duped.</i>

03:19.199 --> 03:22.566
<i>The Party doesn't serve the people,
it serves itself.</i>

03:23.136 --> 03:25.434
<i>We are not at war with Eurasia.</i>

03:26.539 --> 03:29.337
Death! Death! Traitor!

03:30.877 --> 03:33.277
<i>You are being made into obedient...</i>

03:33.380 --> 03:36.213
<i>stupid slaves of the Party.</i>

03:37.384 --> 03:39.284
<i>Open your eyes.</i>

03:39.753 --> 03:42.381
<i>See the evil that is happening to you.</i>

03:43.056 --> 03:46.150
<i>The Party drops bombs on its own citizens.</i>

03:46.259 --> 03:47.226
Traitor!

03:47.327 --> 03:50.854
<i>It is the Party, not the Eurasians,
who are our enemies.</i>

03:52.666 --> 03:53.894
<i>Rise up.</i>

03:54.434 --> 03:56.163
<i>Throw off the yoke.</i>

03:56.670 --> 04:01.164
<i>You have nothing to lose,
and everything to gain.</i>

04:02.309 --> 04:04.573
<i>People of Oceania.</i>

04:35.141 --> 04:36.301
<i>Big, Big, Big....</i>

05:50.283 --> 05:52.308
<i>Innuendo, deleted.</i>

05:53.553 --> 05:55.953
<i>Intransigence, rendered as crime.</i>

05:57.357 --> 05:58.346
<i>Inversion....</i>

07:10.263 --> 07:11.730
Back, Day One.

07:27.247 --> 07:31.308
<i>Ref. Times 1 4-2-84, Page 3,
Byline 2, should read:</i>

07:31.417 --> 07:35.376
<i>"Miniprod Forecasts Increase
Chocolate Ration, April, 1984..."</i>

07:35.488 --> 07:38.252
<i>"from 20 to 25 Grams Per Week."</i>

07:56.409 --> 08:00.175
<i>I confess to spreading the rumor,
on orders from Goldstein...</i>

08:00.847 --> 08:04.374
<i>that the war is not really with Eurasia,
but with Eastasia.</i>

08:05.351 --> 08:09.754
<i>That, for years, in fact since the days
of our glorious Revolution...</i>

08:09.856 --> 08:11.983
<i>I had no faith in our future.</i>

08:13.126 --> 08:16.493
<i>I forged government announcements
and falsified figures...</i>

08:16.596 --> 08:19.827
<i>quoted for agricultural
and industrial production.</i>

08:20.633 --> 08:25.536
<i>As a result of mental disturbance from
my experiences during the atomic wars...</i>

08:26.372 --> 08:29.739
<i>I was a willing subject
of Goldstein's influence.</i>

08:30.577 --> 08:32.977
<i>I was stubborn and egocentric.</i>

08:33.078 --> 08:36.640
<i>When ownlife thoughts occurred to me,
I reveled in them.</i>

08:36.883 --> 08:39.351
<i>I went into the proletarian zones...</i>

08:39.485 --> 08:43.854
<i>I had sex with prostitutes,
I deliberately contracted syphilis.</i>

08:45.225 --> 08:48.524
<i>It was at this time
that I made contact with the Resistance.</i>

08:49.028 --> 08:53.192
<i>I was personally contacted
by the archtraitor, Goldstein...</i>

08:53.299 --> 08:56.462
<i>and ordered to assassinate
certain Inner Party officials.</i>

08:56.569 --> 08:57.593
Bugger!

08:57.704 --> 08:59.035
<i>This I did.</i>

09:00.340 --> 09:04.572
<i>My agents forged documents
and gained entry into the Ministry....</i>

09:04.677 --> 09:06.577
<i>"Thoughtcrime is death."</i>

09:08.014 --> 09:10.482
<i>"Thoughtcrime does not entail death."</i>

09:11.684 --> 09:13.618
<i>"Thoughtcrime is death."</i>

09:15.722 --> 09:19.419
<i>"I have committed,
even before setting pen to paper..."</i>

09:19.993 --> 09:23.087
<i>"the essential crime
that contains all others in itself."</i>

09:23.196 --> 09:27.064
<i>I have spent many hours
of my free time, encouraging my agents...</i>

09:27.166 --> 09:30.567
<i>to deface Party posters
and hoarding announcements.</i>

09:31.437 --> 09:34.338
<i>I read and memorized Goldstein's book.</i>

09:34.941 --> 09:38.934
<i>For 30 years,
I have plotted to bring down the Party.</i>

09:39.479 --> 09:41.504
<i>I was sick in mind and body.</i>

09:42.282 --> 09:46.082
<i>Together with my colleagues,
Aaronson and Rutherford...</i>

09:46.519 --> 09:49.647
<i>I did counterfeit
important Party documents...</i>

09:51.090 --> 09:54.582
<i>including ex-London permits
and travel passes.</i>

09:55.094 --> 09:57.722
<i>And that by use of these documents...</i>

09:58.064 --> 10:01.261
<i>my agents traveled freely
throughout Airstrip One...</i>

10:01.367 --> 10:04.825
<i>encouraging insurrection
and organizing a massive counterplot...</i>

10:04.937 --> 10:08.634
<i>to destroy the innermost faction
of the Oceanian leadership.</i>

10:10.677 --> 10:12.110
<i>Furthermore...</i>

10:13.179 --> 10:17.115
<i>I used my position of privilege
within the Inner Party...</i>

10:17.984 --> 10:20.919
<i>to pervert and betray the truth at all times...</i>

10:21.020 --> 10:25.923
<i>and to suggest, wherever possible,
that our traditional allies in Eastasia...</i>

10:26.759 --> 10:28.784
<i>were in fact, our deadly enemies.</i>

10:29.095 --> 10:32.064
<i>"April the 4th, 1984."</i>

10:32.198 --> 10:34.860
<i>In my position as Chief Factory Planner...</i>

10:35.034 --> 10:36.092
<i>"I think..."</i>

10:36.202 --> 10:38.136
<i>I stole military plans...</i>

10:38.438 --> 10:42.602
<i>and, at vast financial profit,
sold them to the Eurasian leadership.</i>

10:42.742 --> 10:44.369
<i>"...to the past..."</i>

10:45.044 --> 10:46.875
<i>"or to the future..."</i>

10:47.780 --> 10:50.248
<i>"to an age when thought is free."</i>

10:51.517 --> 10:54.315
<i>"From the age of Big Brother..."</i>

10:54.420 --> 10:57.150
<i>"from the age of the Thought Police..."</i>

10:59.325 --> 11:00.952
<i>"from a dead man..."</i>

11:02.628 --> 11:03.925
<i>"greetings!"</i>

11:52.512 --> 11:56.004
<i>30-to-40 group, take your places, please.</i>

11:57.250 --> 12:00.481
<i>Right, let's see which one of us
can touch his toes.</i>

12:00.586 --> 12:03.987
<i>Right over from the hips,
brothers and sisters, please.</i>

12:04.223 --> 12:06.191
<i>One, two.</i>

12:16.169 --> 12:19.764
<i>Smith? 6079, Smith, W.?</i>

12:20.907 --> 12:21.874
<i>Yes, you.</i>

12:22.542 --> 12:23.839
<i>Bend lower.</i>

12:24.877 --> 12:27.243
<i>You're not trying. Watch me.</i>

12:35.788 --> 12:38.279
<i>There, brother. That's what I want.</i>

12:38.925 --> 12:42.452
<i>Anyone under 45 is perfectly
capable of touching his toes.</i>

12:42.829 --> 12:45.229
<i>I'm 39, and I've had four children.</i>

12:45.398 --> 12:48.595
<i>We don't all have the privilege
of fighting in the front line.</i>

12:48.701 --> 12:51.192
<i>Remember our boys on the Malabar Front.</i>

12:51.404 --> 12:54.100
<i>Just think what they have to put up with.</i>

12:55.842 --> 12:59.642
<i>Production of water-heaters
is up 1.5 percent.</i>

13:00.847 --> 13:03.338
<i>Switchgear, 4.5 percent.</i>

13:03.549 --> 13:06.040
<i>Electrical wiring, 10 percent.</i>

13:06.652 --> 13:08.552
<i>Cigarettes, 18 percent.</i>

13:08.754 --> 13:11.052
<i>Bricks, 3 percent.</i>

13:11.390 --> 13:12.914
Morning, Smith.

13:13.025 --> 13:14.219
Parsons.

13:16.262 --> 13:17.820
Heard the rumor?

13:18.064 --> 13:19.622
No. Good news, is it?

13:19.799 --> 13:21.699
I should say so, yes.

13:22.001 --> 13:23.798
Choco rations going up.

13:24.136 --> 13:25.228
Really?

13:25.638 --> 13:27.731
Twenty-five grams next week.

13:28.107 --> 13:29.506
Doubleplus good.

13:30.877 --> 13:33.243
<i>Speakwrites, 14 percent.</i>

13:33.346 --> 13:35.974
<i>Vibra-aging castings, 9 percent.</i>

13:36.282 --> 13:40.582
By the way, Smith, I seem to have run out
of razor blades for some reason.

13:40.720 --> 13:43.450
You wouldn't happen to have any spare,
would you?

13:43.556 --> 13:46.047
I'm sorry, brother. I'm on the last one.

13:46.792 --> 13:48.259
<i>Bandages, 9 percent.</i>

13:48.794 --> 13:51.786
<i>In 1983, Oceania's coal output...</i>

13:51.898 --> 13:54.298
<i>reached 630 million tons.</i>

13:55.234 --> 13:59.830
<i>In 1976, coal output was 605 million tons...</i>

14:00.273 --> 14:02.468
<i>an increase of 4.1 percent.</i>

14:03.309 --> 14:05.903
<i>5.3 million tractors were produced...</i>

14:06.212 --> 14:09.147
<i>an increase of 17.6 percent.</i>

14:10.016 --> 14:11.745
<i>6.1 million trucks...</i>

14:11.851 --> 14:14.615
I wanted to ask you if you've got
any razor blades?

14:14.720 --> 14:16.779
I've tried all over the place.

14:16.889 --> 14:19.687
I've been using the same one for six weeks.

14:19.892 --> 14:23.259
<i>...a staggering increase of 93.4 percent.</i>

14:24.797 --> 14:27.129
Did you see the prisoners
hanged yesterday?

14:27.233 --> 14:30.361
No, I was working.
But I shall see it on the screens.

14:40.980 --> 14:43.312
You'll pick up the gin on the way?

14:46.319 --> 14:47.786
I'll have two.

14:52.558 --> 14:57.086
<i>2.9 million Airstrip One
Mark 5 submachine guns...</i>

14:58.064 --> 15:02.296
<i>3.1 million Grenville gas-operated
light machine guns...</i>

15:02.435 --> 15:03.629
Give me a gin.

15:03.736 --> 15:08.696
<i>2.2 million .5 Victory
recoil-operated heavy machine guns...</i>

15:09.976 --> 15:12.069
<i>6 million rifle grenades...</i>

15:12.178 --> 15:15.614
<i>9 million Perry pineapple pin grenades...</i>

15:15.948 --> 15:18.508
<i>and 1.4 million lightweight...</i>

15:18.618 --> 15:21.678
<i>spigot-launching,
anti-tank rocket projectors.</i>

15:23.155 --> 15:24.816
<i>Food production is also up...</i>

15:24.924 --> 15:28.018
-How's the Newspeak Committee?
-Working overtime.

15:28.294 --> 15:31.320
<i>...butter, 2 percent, milk, 6 percent.</i>

15:31.430 --> 15:34.092
Plusbig waste is in adjectives.

15:35.401 --> 15:39.132
Plusbig problem is timing the language
to scientific advance.

15:43.643 --> 15:46.703
It's a beautiful thing,
the destruction of words.

15:49.048 --> 15:52.506
You won't have seen the Dictionary,
10th edition yet, Smith?

15:52.952 --> 15:54.510
It's that thick.

15:55.221 --> 15:57.883
The 1 1th edition will be that thick.

16:00.359 --> 16:03.851
So the Revolution will be complete
when the language is perfect.

16:03.963 --> 16:08.229
The secret's to move from translation,
to direct thought, to automatic response.

16:08.334 --> 16:12.532
No need for self-discipline.
Language coming from here, not from here.

16:12.738 --> 16:14.228
Excuse me for intruding.

16:14.340 --> 16:17.776
You're saying that we'll be rid of
the last vestiges of Goldsteinism...

16:17.877 --> 16:19.845
when the language has been cleaned.

16:19.945 --> 16:23.346
-I couldn't agree with you more, brother.
-Absolutely.

16:27.286 --> 16:30.414
<i>Praise be to our leader
and the Party workers!</i>

16:34.860 --> 16:37.954
<i>Other munitions production figures
are as follows.</i>

16:38.631 --> 16:41.862
<i>70,000 M-20 tank destroyers...</i>

16:41.967 --> 16:43.992
<i>with 76-mm cannon.</i>

16:45.271 --> 16:46.431
Smith. Syme.

16:50.943 --> 16:53.275
It's encouraging to think that by 2050...

16:53.379 --> 16:57.281
not a single person will be able
to have a conversation like this.

16:57.550 --> 16:58.744
Except the proles?

16:58.851 --> 17:01.376
The proletariat don't count. They're animals.

17:02.221 --> 17:03.984
See the hanging?

17:04.557 --> 17:06.047
Missed it, myself.

17:06.157 --> 17:07.819
Bloody committees.

17:11.497 --> 17:16.093
<i>35,000 Black Eagle 500 cc motorbicycles.</i>

17:19.271 --> 17:21.102
Doubleplus good, this.

17:21.874 --> 17:25.776
You know, I don't think
there's a single piece of meat in this stew.

17:27.313 --> 17:29.781
Looks like meat. Tastes like meat.

17:30.649 --> 17:32.310
It isn't meat at all.

17:32.618 --> 17:34.142
Doubleplus good.

17:35.321 --> 17:36.913
Not like it, Smith?

17:37.022 --> 17:39.047
Yes, it's too rich for me.

17:39.492 --> 17:41.221
Do you mind if i...

17:41.794 --> 17:45.560
<i>Brothers and sisters,
the battle for production has been won.</i>

17:45.765 --> 17:48.632
<i>Completed returns
show that the standard of living...</i>

17:48.734 --> 17:51.897
<i>has risen by no less than 20 percent
over the last year.</i>

17:52.638 --> 17:57.041
<i>All over Oceania there've been spontaneous
demonstrations of Party workers...</i>

17:57.143 --> 17:59.509
<i>voicing their gratitude and joy!</i>

18:00.312 --> 18:04.749
<i>In honor of this massive overfulfillment
of the ninth three-year plan...</i>

18:04.850 --> 18:09.753
<i>it's been announced that chocolate ration
is to be increased to 25 grams per week!</i>

18:18.497 --> 18:20.192
<i>"If there is hope..."</i>

18:20.566 --> 18:22.466
<i>"it lies in the proles."</i>

18:23.435 --> 18:26.233
<i>"If they could become conscious
of their own strength..."</i>

18:26.338 --> 18:29.000
<i>"they would have no need to conspire."</i>

18:29.341 --> 18:31.605
<i>"History does not matter to them."</i>

18:42.388 --> 18:44.253
<i>"It was three years ago..."</i>

18:45.524 --> 18:47.287
<i>"on a dark evening."</i>

18:48.327 --> 18:50.295
<i>"Easy to slip the patrols."</i>

18:50.763 --> 18:53.493
<i>"And I'd gone into the proletarian areas."</i>

18:56.969 --> 19:00.336
<i>"There was no one else in the street,
and no telescreens."</i>

19:06.478 --> 19:08.378
<i>"She said, '$2.'"</i>

19:11.150 --> 19:12.845
<i>"So I went with her."</i>

19:16.422 --> 19:18.219
<i>"She had a young face..."</i>

19:19.525 --> 19:21.117
<i>"painted very thick."</i>

19:24.830 --> 19:27.230
<i>"It was really the paint that appealed to me..."</i>

19:27.333 --> 19:29.631
<i>"the whiteness of it, like a mask..."</i>

19:30.469 --> 19:32.437
<i>"and the bright red lips."</i>

19:35.608 --> 19:36.802
Come on.

19:52.224 --> 19:54.215
<i>"There were no preliminaries."</i>

19:55.494 --> 19:59.590
<i>"Standing there, with the scent
of dead insects and cheap perfume..."</i>

19:59.698 --> 20:02.531
<i>"I went ahead and did it, just the same."</i>

21:04.563 --> 21:06.360
Rutherford unperson.

21:06.632 --> 21:08.259
Substitute Ogilvy.

21:09.168 --> 21:11.500
Ogilvy bio, details as follows:

21:12.338 --> 21:13.635
"War hero."

21:14.073 --> 21:16.371
"Recently killed, Malabar Front."

21:16.976 --> 21:21.072
<i>"Today awarded posthumous
Order of Conspicuous Merit, Second Class."</i>

21:29.555 --> 21:31.750
<i>I accuse myself of sabotage...</i>

21:32.391 --> 21:34.757
<i>embezzlement of Party funds...</i>

21:35.260 --> 21:37.455
<i>sale of military secrets...</i>

21:37.563 --> 21:40.657
<i>of being in the pay
of the Government of Eurasia...</i>

21:40.766 --> 21:44.258
<i>of being a sexual pervert
and a thoughtcriminal.</i>

21:46.105 --> 21:49.734
<i>I exploited my trusted position
at the Ministry of Peace...</i>

21:49.908 --> 21:52.536
<i>to mislead our allies in Eastasia...</i>

21:53.112 --> 21:58.072
<i>and also to corrupt youth by means
of seditious literature and drugs.</i>

22:01.487 --> 22:03.682
<i>I am guilty on all counts.</i>

22:04.790 --> 22:06.052
<i>I stand here...</i>

22:06.158 --> 22:08.251
<i>a victim of the influence of....</i>

22:08.360 --> 22:10.920
<i>"Under the spreading chestnut tree..."</i>

22:11.530 --> 22:12.861
<i>"I sold you..."</i>

22:13.565 --> 22:15.055
<i>"you sold me."</i>

22:17.169 --> 22:18.727
<i>And I ask only...</i>

22:19.838 --> 22:21.066
<i>for you to accept...</i>

22:22.141 --> 22:23.938
<i>my love of our leader.</i>

23:59.138 --> 24:00.628
Can I help you?

24:05.811 --> 24:07.438
Anything special?

24:08.614 --> 24:09.876
I was here before.

24:11.383 --> 24:12.816
Razor blades.

24:15.454 --> 24:17.354
You sold me the notebook.

24:17.456 --> 24:18.480
Yes.

24:21.393 --> 24:22.655
Please look around.

24:49.321 --> 24:50.686
What's this?

24:52.090 --> 24:53.921
It's a beautiful thing.

24:54.893 --> 24:56.588
Over 100 years old.

25:00.365 --> 25:02.162
Cost you $4.

25:20.185 --> 25:23.677
There's another room upstairs
that you might like to see.

25:24.122 --> 25:26.147
But there's not much in it.

25:27.259 --> 25:28.886
Just a few things.

26:02.561 --> 26:04.119
My woman's dead.

26:04.930 --> 26:07.592
I'm just trying to sell the furniture.

26:12.804 --> 26:14.567
It's a beautiful bed...

26:15.040 --> 26:17.406
if you can get the bugs out of it.

26:28.420 --> 26:30.217
Interested in old prints at all?

26:36.862 --> 26:40.298
The frame's fixed to the wall,
but I daresay I could unscrew it.

26:40.399 --> 26:42.526
How did this escape?

26:43.435 --> 26:45.062
I know what it is.

26:45.737 --> 26:49.468
It's the museum in the street
outside the Palace of Justice.

26:49.908 --> 26:54.368
"Oranges and lemons,
say the bells of St. Clement's"

26:54.780 --> 26:56.247
What was that?

26:58.417 --> 26:59.884
Something old.

27:27.879 --> 27:29.278
<i>War is peace!</i>

27:30.449 --> 27:32.144
<i>Freedom is slavery!</i>

27:32.984 --> 27:34.815
<i>Ignorance is strength!</i>

